article.description: USC had the late-game heroics this time against Stanford, scoring the game's final six points Saturday for a 54-49 victory.
article.headline: USC avenges earlier loss to Stanford by scoring last 6 points of game
article.linkText: USC turns tables on Stanford with late heroics

inlines.body:
More On USC

For the latest news on all things USC, check out the Trojans blog. Blog

article.story: LOS ANGELES -- USC had the late-game heroics this time against Stanford, avenging an earlier one-point road loss by scoring the game's final six points Saturday for a 54-49 victory. The big man for USC (14-9, 6-5 Pac-10) in every way was 6-foot-10 sophomore Nikola Vucevic, whose 18th and final point came on his 14th rebound after a missed Marcus Johnson drive with 26.4 seconds left. That score came after four USC tip-in attempts and gave the Trojans the lead for good at 50-49. Stanford (10-13, 4-7), which has yet to win a Pac-10 road game in seven attempts, missed a jump shot and a free throw down the stretch, and USC closed it out with four straight free throws. Landry Fields led the Cardinal with a 27 points and 11 rebounds.
